  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.5.9-stable`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI would expect to sync in a reasonable pace.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nTaking a long time to sync testnet ropsten since blocks higher than #500000. Around 0.7Mg/s.\r\n\r\nI'm running in a Ubuntu 16.04 server with 18GB of RAM memory, and basically I noticed the syncing process of my geth client has gotten really slow, importing 1 block per time at the pace above mentioned. \r\n\r\nThe command I'm using is:\r\n`geth --networkid 3 --rpc --rpcaddr \"0.0.0.0\" --rpcapi eth,web3,debug --ws --wsaddr \"0.0.0.0\" --wsorigins \"*\" --wsapi eth,web3,debug --cache=1024 --fast --jitvm`\r\n\r\nIs there any specific reason why this is happening?\r\n\r\n\r\n",
